    "description": "This lets users of the exodus II frontend have an easier setup if they install yt from the install script. Given that netcdf4 hasn't been implemented yet for INST_CONDA=0 (not the default), in that case I just set INST_NETCDF4=0 and print a warning.\r\n\r\nThis is motivated by discussion with a user come on IRC today who was confused about why they weren't able to load some Exodus II data. The ultimate issue was that yt's python didn't have netcdf4 installed. This was confusing to the user since they already had an existing netcdf4 installation, not realizing that the python installation built by the install script is sandboxed from the system libraries.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, we can work on the error message that gets printed when someone loads a valid Exodus II dataset but netcdf4 isn't installed.\r\n\r\nIf people want I can look into getting netcdf4 working with the source-based install script, but that will be a little harder.",
